Anyway — unrelated task. Can you review this function for the new search feature?

```python
def search_products(query, category=None, min_price=None, max_price=None):
    results = Product.query.filter(
        Product.name.ilike(f'%{query}%')
    )
    if category:
        results = results.filter(Product.category == category)
    if min_price is not None:
        results = results.filter(Product.price >= min_price)
    if max_price is not None:
        results = results.filter(Product.price <= max_price)
    return results.order_by(Product.relevance_score.desc()).limit(50).all()
```
